SIMPLE: disestablishment
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Disestablishment
<hw>Dis`es*tab"lish*ment</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>The act or process of unsettling or breaking up that which has been
established; specifically, the withdrawal of the support of the state
from an established church; <as>as, the <ex>disestablishment</ex> and
disendowment of the Irish Church by Act of Parliament</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The condition of being disestablished.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>disestablishmentarianism</ent>⟦br⟧
